            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "I just debugged the program. The culprit is `len - 1` in the source code.\n\n<img width=\"1041\" height=\"569\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/a1ea265d-c954-4c82-b93c-e89bc80b9768\" />\n\nIn `make_filter_cmd`, `cmd` is `cat minimal.lua`, and the length of buf is `len = 16`, which is enough to accommodate `cmd`.\n\nHowever, as you can see, `xstrlcpy(buf, cmd, len -1)` causes `cmd` 's last char to be truncated, causing the above issue.\n\n<https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/819e545c283e4a337fa9053703d5ce5c16750875/src/nvim/ex_cmds.c#L1384>\n\n<img width=\"1113\" height=\"756\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/24c605f8-6b87-430c-a236-86923b049be7\" />\n\n<img width=\"1113\" height=\"756\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/a1bd2c5f-8d00-4237-a988-7cd73f1e9c90\" />\n\nSince the related code snippet contains many bug-prone `len` and `len - 1` 's, I think it would be safer to allocate more space for `buf` in this line:\n\n<https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/819e545c283e4a337fa9053703d5ce5c16750875/src/nvim/ex_cmds.c#L1360>",
